laboratory_examinations.findings: ECG shows ST-segment elevation myocardial infarction due to proximal left anterior descending coronary artery (LAD) occlusion located before the first diagonal (D1) and first septal (S1) branches.
Confirmed proximal left anterior descending coronary artery (LAD) occlusion.
Implantation of 2 stents: 1 in the proximal LAD (Xience 3×23 mm) and the other in the mid-LAD (Xience 2.5×18 mm) with very good results.
